      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ELLIOTTO (2) didn't fire a shot last start at Terang but was much better the start prior when chasing gamely into the placings in what has proven a hot race. Backs up quickly and drops to a more suitable trip. Opperman back on is a big tick. AUSSIE PHAROAH (5) is knocking on the door. Has placed in his last two, savaging the line last time at Ararat when coming from a long way off them. Will appreciate the extra trip, though will likely get a long way back from the draw again. Watch for him late. EXOTIC DANCER (7) gets a welcome drop in grade and is on the quick back-up. Has peaks that measure up and is drawn kindly. Worth some thought. PIWHANE (8) is mixing his form and can cause a late scare if the tempo is genuine. BLISSFUL BAY (9) was good two back but failed here last time. Blinkers go on to sharpen him up. Wary of improvement.",
